msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/cult_fanatic.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Armor Class** 13 (leather armor)    \n"
"**Hit Points** 33 (6d8 + 6)    \n"
"**Speed** 30 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/cult_fanatic.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 11 (+0) | 14 (+2) | 12 (+1) | 10 (+0) | 13 (+1) | 14 (+2) |   \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/cult_fanatic.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Deception +4, Persuasion +4, Religion +2    \n"
"**Senses** passive Perception 11    \n"
"**Languages** any one language (usually Common)    \n"
"**Challenge** 2 (450 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/cult_fanatic.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Dark Devotion.** The fanatic has advantage on saving throws against being "
"charmed or frightened.    \n"
"**Spellcasting.** The fanatic is a 4th-level spellcaster. Its spellcasting "
"ability is Wisdom (spell save DC 11, +3 to hit with spell attacks). The "
"fanatic has the following cleric spells prepared:    \n"
"Cantrips (at will): **_light, sacred flame, thaumaturgy_**    \n"
"1st level (4 slots): **_command, inflict wounds, shield of faith_**    \n"
"2nd level (3 slots): **_hold person, spiritual weapon_** \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/cult_fanatic.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions \n"
"**Multiattack.** The fanatic makes two melee attacks.    \n"
"**Dagger.** _Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range "
"20/60 ft., one creature. _Hit:_ 4 (1d4 + 2) piercing damage. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/cult_fanatic.md:32
msgid ""
"### Description Fanatics are often part of a cult's leadership, using their "
"charisma and dogma to influence and prey on those of weak will. Most are "
"interested in personal power above all else."
msgstr ""
